CRITICAL OPERATIONAL LESSON (iter37, 2026-06-07) - DO NOT kill a healthy watcher to force a version upgrade: this fire showed update_available 0.1.636->0.1.637, and I killed the working 0.1.636 watcher + supervisor to force the upgrade. The 0.1.637 wasm download (149MB) repeatedly ABORTED on flaky TLS, and the bunx/npx cache served stale gm-plugkit 2.0.1536 (vs npm 2.0.1537), so every `bun x gm-plugkit@latest spool` re-hit the failing fetch and NEVER fell back to the cached 0.1.636 - leaving the spool with NO live watcher for ~30 min of recovery churn (multiple competing boots, stale .watcher.lock holding the dead pid 21224, ensure-ready aborted). RECOVERY THAT WORKED: kill ALL plugkit procs, rm the stale .watcher.lock + .status.json, then run the INSTALLED wrapper DIRECTLY on the cached wasm bypassing the bootstrap fetch: `bun ~/.gm-tools/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js spool` - this came up immediately on cached 0.1.636 (pid 22060, version_drifted=false) because it skips ensureReady's remote 0.1.637 download. STANDING RULES: (1) NEVER kill a functional watcher to chase a version upgrade - the supervisor's own version-change path handles upgrades on a clean download; an update_available is not a reason to manually recycle a healthy watcher. (2) When the bootstrap is stuck fetching a new wasm (flaky network), recover by running the installed gm-tools wrapper directly on the cached wasm (`bun ~/.gm-tools/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js spool`) - this is the offline-equivalent fallback the CLI does not expose as a flag. (3) The gm_plugkit_stale field in the instruction response gives the exact cache-clear fix: `bun pm cache rm; npm cache clean --force; rm -rf ~/AppData/Local/npm-cache/_npx ~/.bun/install/cache; bun x gm-plugkit@latest --kill-stale-watchers; bun x gm-plugkit@latest spool` - but that still needs the 0.1.637 download to succeed, so it is blocked by the same flaky network. The 0.1.637 upgrade is DEFERRED to a clean-network boot (the supervisor will take it via version-change when the download completes); the watcher serves all verbs fine on 0.1.636 meanwhile. The phase/PRD state survived all the watcher churn intact (durable on-disk), re-validating that design.